The Windfall pygidia exhibit two obvious ontogenetic progressions. First, minute spines present opposite the terminal axial piece on the smallest specimens (
Plate 5.15
) are lost during ontogeny. Further, in the smallest specimens the posterior margin is an even curve, becoming progressively more embayed with a distinct bilobed appearance evident in larger specimens.

